# OPSEU / CAAT Branding (Reference Tenant #1)

## Product context
This comms toolbox is a **complementary volunteer tool** for local union communicators. OPSEU/SEFPO does not provide basic local-level social media branding, logo export, or graphic generation — locals fill that gap themselves. This hub exists to make that work easier while respecting official brand guidelines.

Strike/crisis comms live at `/guide/crisis` (not top nav) — OPSEU/local-focused high-level guidance for volunteer comms leads.

## Official OPSEU colours
Source: [OPSEU graphics & letterhead templates](https://opseu.org/information/opseu-graphics-logos-and-letterhead-templates/12263)

| Token | Hex | Use |
|-------|-----|-----|
| OPSEU Blue | `#003DA5` | Pantone 285 — primary union brand colour |
| OPSEU Dark | `#002868` | Depth, hover states, accent text on light backgrounds |
| White | `#FFFFFF` | Graphics accent on blue/dark backgrounds (quote cards, flyers, logo builder) |

**UI shell** (header, buttons, focus rings) should lead with OPSEU blue. Reserve white for graphic-tool accents on brand-coloured backgrounds — never as the default chrome colour.

## Logo sources
1. **Official pack** — `public/assets/caat-opseu/logo-primary.png` via `DEFAULT_ASSET_PACK_PATH` (default OPSEU/SEFPO lockup, Pantone 285)
2. **Custom upload** — PNG, JPEG, WebP, or SVG stored as `customLogoDataUrl` in `BrandKit` (localStorage via `DataAdapter`)
3. **Platform UnionOps mark** — interlocking lowercase **u** + **o**. Live chrome uses the monochrome PNG (`public/assets/unionops/logo-mark-interlock.png`) via CSS mask in `UnionOpsMark`: **primary** plate + **graphics accent** glyph; `onDark` / Brand Kit dark preview swaps the back plate to **white** and the glyph to primary. SVG fallbacks remain under `public/assets/unionops/*.svg`. Source rasters: `public/assets/unionops/source/`.

Use `BrandLogo` for display; use `LogoSettings` for the official/custom toggle + upload UI. Favicon: `src/app/icon.png`. Twitter/OG: `src/app/opengraph-image.tsx` / `twitter-image.tsx`.

## Defaults
First-visit Brand Kit colours come from `config/host-brand.json` / `NEXT_PUBLIC_BRAND_*` via `resolveHostBrandDefaults()` → `BRAND_COLORS` / `DEFAULT_BRAND_KIT`. OPSEU blue lives in the reference tenant seed and the OPSEU union preset — not as the platform default for new hosts.

## Multi-union rule
No OPSEU names or hex values in new core components. Reference tenant seed + cursor rules only. Other unions supply their own `brandDefaults` and asset packs in Phase 1+.
